President Biden spoke at Boston Logan International Airport in Massachusetts, highlighting the historic investment being made in airport infrastructure. He emphasized the importance of investing in American workers and unions, stating that American union workers are the best trained in the world. The President announced that $62 million will be invested in upgrading Terminal E at Logan Airport, which will create 5,900 union jobs and improve capacity, accessibility, and energy efficiency. He also discussed the broader economic plan to grow the economy from the bottom up and invest in America's infrastructure, clean energy future, and innovation economy. President Biden stressed the need for the United States to regain its position as a global leader in infrastructure and technology, and urged Americans to remember their capacity to achieve anything when they come together.